Kwale town residents have threatened to storm into Governor Salim Mvurya and Kwale Water and Sewerage Company MD Athman Chembea's offices and close them, as they have not received water for a week.Residents have accused the county Water department and the water company of being incompetent in providing services.Led by Tsimba Golini MCA hopeful Festus Mwaniki, the residents yesterday gave the firm and county three days to provide them water.For months, residents have received inconsistent water supply.Speaking to the Star in Kwale yesterday, Mwaniki said that locals in the area have been left with the only option of using untreated boreholes and well water exposing them to health hazards.